lines.text: I had the pleasure of seeing your patient, Mekail Hayati, who was seen and reviewed by our intake team
She presented to follow up on DM2. Mother and relatives on mom's side have diabetes. Brother has diabetes
He was started on Metformin 500mg PO BID in Jan 2025 and then optimized to metformin 1g PO BID in Apr
2025. He is tolerating well. He did not do any blood tests but reports that FBG are "5-7s" and pc meals are
"<8s" no symptoms of hyper/hypoglycemia. He has made significant changes in lifestyle as well, exercises
regularly and is doing intermittent fasting eating only 1 meal daily. His weight has reduced about 3kg, BMI 38.1
- L: eats at 4pm: chicken; biryani; rice/meat/vegetables
Activity pattern: 3 days/week outside or gym in his building doing various activities. Was a wrestler previously.
Started ramipril and rosuvastatin 1m ago with FD.
Retinopathy: no dilated eye exam previously. Has had vision tested in 2025.
No symptoms of ischemic heart disease. FD sent to cardiologist. Patient has had stress test which was normal.
Holter was done which was normal.
Recently completed. Head and neck exam was normal.
Cardiovascular examination showed normal heart sounds, regular rate and rhythm, no audible murmurs or
Peripheral fine touch sensation was intact to 10gm monofilament.
Feet were clear to inspection. Pedal pulses palpable.
